The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, visited Mt. Pleasant Baptist Church in Opelousas, Louisiana, along with other public officials, to express support and solidarity after a series of fires destroyed several churches in the area. Pence condemned the attacks on communities of faith and stated that no one should fear for their safety in a place of worship. He commended the resilience and faith of the affected churches and the community, and praised their response of charity and forgiveness. Pence assured them that the American people stand with them and that the churches will be rebuilt. The Vice President emphasized the importance of love and unity, stating that the foundation of faith in these churches remains strong. He expressed confidence in the future of these churches and faith in Louisiana and America.